Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of Bayesian networks for modelling the effectiveness of curriculum in educational systems, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of user behavior and logs, which could fall under the sub-categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with the complexity of curriculum planning, which could be considered as a cybernetics and systems sub-category (cs.CY).
